+### FlowerHub data path
+
+The `/flowerhub` ops view reads four files from a local staffroom data directory.
+
+**Default path (no env var set):**
+```
+/Users/glenkirkham/flowerhub-staffroom-data/data
+```
+
+**Override via env var** (add to `.env.local`):
+```env
+FLOWERHUB_DATA_DIR=/path/to/your/staffroom-data/data
+```
+
+**If your data lives at `/Users/glenkirkham/staffroom-sync`**, use either approach:
+
+*Option A â€” set the env var:*
+```env
+FLOWERHUB_DATA_DIR=/Users/glenkirkham/staffroom-sync/data
+```
+
+*Option B â€” create a symlink so the default path resolves automatically:*
+```bash
+ln -sfn /Users/glenkirkham/staffroom-sync /Users/glenkirkham/flowerhub-staffroom-data
+```
+
+**Sanity check** â€” run this before starting the dev server to confirm all four files are reachable:
+```bash
+DIR="${FLOWERHUB_DATA_DIR:-/Users/glenkirkham/flowerhub-staffroom-data/data}"
+for f in active_tasks.json OFFICE-BOARD.md TASK-BOARD.md inbox_queue.json; do
+  test -f "$DIR/$f" && echo "âś“ $f" || echo "âś— MISSING: $f"
+done
+```
+
+All four should print `âś“`. Any `âś—` means the path is wrong â€” fix `FLOWERHUB_DATA_DIR` or create the symlink before proceeding.
+
