 ## Troubleshooting
 
-If the UI loads but Connect fails, the problem is usually on the Studio -> Gateway side:
+### `/flowerhub` shows all panels as MISSING
+
+The API route (`/api/flowerhub-ops`) could not read the staffroom data files. Path mismatch is
+the most common cause.
+
+**First check:** run the sanity check from the [FlowerHub data path](#flowerhub-data-path) section
+to confirm all four files are reachable from your current `FLOWERHUB_DATA_DIR`.
+
+**Cache note:** the API route caches responses for 30 seconds. After fixing the path, wait up to
+30s or restart the dev server for panels to switch from MISSING to LIVE.
+
+**Quick API probe:**
+```bash
+curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/flowerhub-ops | python3 -m json.tool | grep -A2 '"sources"'
+```
+Each source should show `"status": "LIVE"`. If all show `"MISSING"`, the data directory is wrong.
+If one shows `"STALE"`, the corresponding file hasn't been updated within its threshold
+(active\_tasks: 10 min Â· inbox\_queue: 60 min Â· board files: 24 h).
+
+---
+
+### If the UI loads but Connect fails, the problem is usually on the Studio -> Gateway side:
 
 - Confirm the upstream URL and token in Studio settings.
 - `EPROTO` or `wrong version number` usually means `wss://` was used against a non-TLS endpoint.
